50|$|A <b>pilonidal</b> cyst can {{resemble}} a dermoid cyst, {{a kind of}} teratoma (germ cell tumor). In particular, a <b>pilonidal</b> cyst in the gluteal cleft can {{resemble a}} sacrococcygeal teratoma. Correct diagnosis is important because all teratomas require complete surgical excision, if possible without any spillage, and consultation with an oncologist.|$|E
